g.text: If you are displaying (like a list, or drop down, or whatever) "reference data" from another API:
- your best best is DO NOT STORE THAT IN MEMORY AT ALL.
- You can't change it, and you should request it as late as possible so it is "fresh"
- This is a problem with throwing everything in a store (which we are going to do in a minute).
Add it to the Ngrx Store
refreshing when the store is created (so where you provide it)
wanted to share that across multiple components
then I wouldn't even use a SignalStore.
